#include <iostream>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    int numer=0, denom=0;
    for(int i=1; i<=n/2; i++){
        if(__gcd(i,n-i)==1){
            numer=i;
            denom=n-i;
        }
    }
    cout<<numer<<" "<<denom;
    return 0;
}



alchemy:
to find the extra crystals that we need. We add the extra yellow and blue crystals that we need. To find the extra yellow crystals, we 
subtract the yellow crystals that we have by 2 times yellow balls & green balls

Yellow Crystal = Yellow Crystal we have - 2* Yellow Ball - Green Ball
Blue Crystal   = Blue Crystal - 3*Blue Ball - Green Ball

fraction:
in this case, we want to find 2 numbers that we add together is n. The numbers should also be coprime. n be ireducible proper fraction.
